This repo builds a small compiler pipeline: `dict.steno` (a fenced steno-DSL source file, the single source of truth for stroke definitions) is compiled by `crates/steno` into JSON artifacts under `out/`, which are consumed by Plover (dictionaries) and by the `nvim/` Lua plugin (stroke/snippet tables) and by `viz/` (a standalone HTML stroke-tree explorer). `docs/` is the normative spec for that pipeline — grammar in `steno-format.md`, pass architecture in `pipeline.md`, settled TS-vs-Rust precedent in `porting-notes.md` — checked before editing `crates/steno/src`, with code winning over doc on disagreement. `scripts/ci.sh` plus `.github/workflows/` enforce the project's hard constraints (no unsafe, no external deps, workspace lint hygiene) as CI gates. `Cargo.lock` currently resolves to zero dependencies, consistent with the "no runtime dependencies" rule.

A typical cross-cutting change starts in `dict.steno` (adding/altering a stroke entry or directive) and must be checked against three things simult